folder: North Hempstead Turn & 150th Street, Queens, NY
text:
North Hempstead Turnpike, at the N.W. corner of 150th Street, showing the T. Whitson farmhouse from 1860-1891, in a set of four views. This structure was built in 1812. No. 3, of this set shows the barn and sheds at the rear of the house.

1-2-3 January 1923.
4 August 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

folder: North Hempstead Turn & 150th Street, Queens, NY
text:
North Hempstead Turnpike, at the N.W. corner of 150th Street (Oak Ave.), showing the T. Whitson house from 1873 to 1891. Thomas Wood was the occupant in 1896. This is a set of three views from slightly different angles.

January 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
